1
00:00:15,750 --> 00:00:18,041
Koyuki and... you?

2
00:00:18,125 --> 00:00:19,083
But how?

3
00:00:19,166 --> 00:00:22,666
[YUU gasps]
This isn't how it looks.

4
00:00:22,750 --> 00:00:24,500
[FUUKA gasps]

5
00:00:24,583 --> 00:00:27,500
[YUU gasps] Wait, Akitsuki!
Let me explain!

6
00:00:29,666 --> 00:00:31,375
[YUU gasps]

7
00:00:38,625 --> 00:00:40,083
[KOYUKI sighs]

8
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:51,458
♪

9
00:01:02,708 --> 00:01:04,000
<i>The place that I always dreamed</i>

10
00:01:04,083 --> 00:01:06,958
<i>I'd reach one day</i>
<i>is too high above us</i>

11
00:01:07,041 --> 00:01:08,041
<i>To get to</i>

12
00:01:08,125 --> 00:01:10,250
<i>The promise we made is fading</i>

13
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:13,375
<i>every moment we</i>
<i>conform like they do</i>

14
00:01:13,458 --> 00:01:14,750
<i>I wanna move on my own</i>

15
00:01:14,833 --> 00:01:16,125
<i>Step away from the crowd</i>

16
00:01:16,208 --> 00:01:17,583
<i>I wanna dance to my own beat</i>

17
00:01:17,666 --> 00:01:19,958
<i>I'm done trying to blend in</i>

18
00:01:21,166 --> 00:01:23,750
<i>I won't be tied</i>
<i>to a tedious world</i>

19
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:26,583
<i>Repeating each day like</i>
<i>a broken record sickens me</i>

20
00:01:26,666 --> 00:01:29,125
<i>(No matter how I try</i>
<i>I can't escape repetition)</i>

21
00:01:29,208 --> 00:01:30,250
<i>It's hard to change it up</i>

22
00:01:30,333 --> 00:01:31,833
<i>When no one else is listening</i>

23
00:01:31,916 --> 00:01:33,625
<i>We're in a box, stuck in a box</i>

24
00:01:33,708 --> 00:01:36,166
<i>Meant to stifle what we feel</i>

25
00:01:36,250 --> 00:01:38,916
<i>Forced to erase all</i>
<i>that we know is real</i>

26
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,166
<i>But I refuse to be locked up</i>

27
00:01:40,250 --> 00:01:41,250
<i>Won't live in this prison</i>

28
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:43,166
<i>Gotta fight for open skies</i>

29
00:01:44,375 --> 00:01:45,958
<i>Time to break free</i>

30
00:01:46,041 --> 00:01:49,916
<i>Open our hearts to a world and</i>
<i>go racing forward to the light</i>

31
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,666
<i>These broken chains</i>
<i>can't hold us back</i>

32
00:01:51,750 --> 00:01:55,666
<i>We're finally on track to heal</i>
<i>all the fractures in ourselves</i>

33
00:01:55,750 --> 00:01:57,041
<i>As we climb and ascend</i>

34
00:01:57,125 --> 00:01:58,375
<i>Aiming high to the end</i>

35
00:01:58,458 --> 00:02:00,833
<i>We'll feel a climber's high</i>

36
00:02:00,916 --> 00:02:03,666
<i>Hear these words and know your</i>
<i>dream can be stronger than steel</i>

37
00:02:03,750 --> 00:02:04,875
<i>Just believe</i>

38
00:02:04,958 --> 00:02:05,666
<i>You have the power</i>

39
00:02:05,750 --> 00:02:09,291
<i>Let your voice be heard</i>

40
00:02:09,375 --> 00:02:14,333
♪

41
00:02:23,666 --> 00:02:25,791
[footsteps]

42
00:02:25,875 --> 00:02:28,958
You're totally soaked!
What happened to you?

43
00:02:29,041 --> 00:02:31,333
Yeah. I guess it was raining
harder than I thought.

44
00:02:31,416 --> 00:02:32,750
[laughs]

45
00:02:32,833 --> 00:02:35,208
I bet you can't even
tell I used an umbrella!

46
00:02:35,291 --> 00:02:36,625
Yep, that's a fact.

47
00:02:36,708 --> 00:02:39,125
You should prob'ly dry
off and get changed, huh?

48
00:02:39,208 --> 00:02:40,583
Yeah.

49
00:02:41,750 --> 00:02:44,000
Hey, didn't he come
back with you?

50
00:02:45,250 --> 00:02:46,875
[FUUKA]
Couldn't find him.

51
00:02:51,541 --> 00:02:53,083
[MIKASA]
Huh?

52
00:02:59,291 --> 00:03:02,500
Tama, are you okay?

53
00:03:02,583 --> 00:03:07,833
[KOYUKI gasps] I'm sorry,
I just slipped, that's all.

54
00:03:07,916 --> 00:03:09,458
So, who's your friend?

55
00:03:09,541 --> 00:03:12,791
Is she the one you're
starting a band with?

56
00:03:12,875 --> 00:03:14,583
[YUU]
Well, yeah,

57
00:03:16,083 --> 00:03:21,125
We might've given her the
wrong idea. I mean, after all...

58
00:03:21,208 --> 00:03:23,750
...you and I are
just friends, aren't we?

59
00:03:30,083 --> 00:03:31,291
[YUU]
What a mess.

60
00:03:31,375 --> 00:03:34,375
She definitely got
the wrong idea.

61
00:03:34,458 --> 00:03:36,375
[footsteps]

62
00:03:37,708 --> 00:03:41,750
[gasps]
There you are!

63
00:03:41,833 --> 00:03:44,791
Listen, do you think we could
talk about last night?

64
00:03:44,875 --> 00:03:46,291
[grunts]

65
00:03:47,916 --> 00:03:49,333
[YUU gasps]

66
00:03:49,416 --> 00:03:51,333
Sorry if I messed
up your evening.

67
00:03:51,416 --> 00:03:52,583
Don't worry, I won't tell.

68
00:03:52,666 --> 00:03:55,916
Wha--? Wait, No!
You've got it all mixed up!

69
00:03:57,083 --> 00:03:58,166
[FUUKA]
Which part?

70
00:03:58,250 --> 00:03:59,958
Tama and I--

71
00:04:00,041 --> 00:04:02,666
Koyuki, I mean.
We're really just friends.

72
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:05,416
[FUUKA grunts]
If that's true,

73
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:07,375
then why didn't you
tell me you knew her?

74
00:04:07,458 --> 00:04:08,625
[YUU]
I don't know.

75
00:04:08,708 --> 00:04:10,458
I was looking for the
right time to say it.

76
00:04:10,541 --> 00:04:12,041
You had plenty of chances!

77
00:04:12,125 --> 00:04:14,625
You could've done it at
the movie, or at her concert...

78
00:04:14,708 --> 00:04:16,333
[gasps]

79
00:04:16,416 --> 00:04:17,750
Just forget it!

80
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:19,291
Akitsuki!

81
00:04:20,875 --> 00:04:22,625
[clattering]

82
00:04:22,708 --> 00:04:25,250
Uh-oh. What's goin'
on over here?

83
00:04:25,333 --> 00:04:28,416
A little teen drama?

84
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:29,625
Earth to Yuu?

85
00:04:29,708 --> 00:04:31,625
You spacin' out, "Teen Drama"?

86
00:04:31,708 --> 00:04:32,958
[YUU exhales]

87
00:04:36,375 --> 00:04:37,458
[GUY A]
Excuse me, miss!

88
00:04:37,541 --> 00:04:39,916
[GUY B]
Can I order?

89
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,791
[YUU]
Uh. Hey, could--

90
00:04:45,583 --> 00:04:47,750
[YUU]
What is with her?

91
00:04:47,833 --> 00:04:49,583
Which guitar do you
think we should get?

92
00:04:49,666 --> 00:04:51,000
[MIKASA]
First we should probably decide

93
00:04:51,083 --> 00:04:52,000
who's playing what.

94
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:53,750
Yeah, guess you're right!

95
00:04:53,833 --> 00:04:56,250
[MIKASA laughs] Got a little
ahead of yourself, there.

96
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:59,708
[FUUKA laughs]
I'm just so excited!

97
00:05:05,666 --> 00:05:08,291
I love this time of day, when
we're finally past the rush.

98
00:05:08,375 --> 00:05:11,041
[MIKASA sighs] Yeah, me too,
but it's a lot easier now.

99
00:05:11,125 --> 00:05:13,333
[YAHAGI]
Easier, huh? Good to know.

100
00:05:13,416 --> 00:05:16,125
I'd be happy to give you
some extra work tomorrow!

101
00:05:16,208 --> 00:05:17,375
Thanks for the dinner!

102
00:05:17,458 --> 00:05:19,250
[YAHAGI]
Huh? Sure.

103
00:05:29,041 --> 00:05:30,583
[YUU sighs]

104
00:05:42,375 --> 00:05:43,583
[FUUKA gasps]

105
00:05:43,666 --> 00:05:45,458
Something happened between
you two, didn't it?

106
00:05:45,541 --> 00:05:48,541
[gasps] No, I don't
know what you mean.

107
00:05:48,625 --> 00:05:51,500
I think you do. It's obvious
when you're together.

108
00:05:51,583 --> 00:05:53,666
[FUUKA grunts]

109
00:05:53,750 --> 00:05:55,458
Wanna talk about it?

110
00:05:59,250 --> 00:06:02,291
It's just that we're
having a little tiff.

111
00:06:07,375 --> 00:06:10,791
[YUU grunts]
Akitsuki, watch it, will you?

112
00:06:10,875 --> 00:06:12,500
[GIRL A]
Oops! Sorry about that!

113
00:06:12,583 --> 00:06:14,125
Watch where you're
going next time!

114
00:06:14,208 --> 00:06:15,416
Shut up, I was!

115
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:16,458
[GIRLS laugh]

116
00:06:16,541 --> 00:06:19,000
[GIRL B]
Did you see his face?

117
00:06:19,083 --> 00:06:21,000
Wanna come play with me?

118
00:06:22,666 --> 00:06:24,791
I can't let this go on.

119
00:06:32,166 --> 00:06:33,750
[YUU]
Akitsuki!

120
00:06:36,375 --> 00:06:38,041
What do you want?

121
00:06:43,875 --> 00:06:44,833
I'm sorry!

122
00:06:44,916 --> 00:06:47,041
Huh?

123
00:06:47,125 --> 00:06:50,083
[YUU] That's what I wanted.
To apologize.

124
00:06:50,166 --> 00:06:51,333
[grunts]

125
00:06:53,333 --> 00:06:56,666
Koyuki and I were, we were
friends when we were younger.

126
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:59,000
And we reconnected
on Twitter recently.

127
00:06:59,083 --> 00:07:01,208
But, see, she was using
a private account,

128
00:07:01,291 --> 00:07:03,041
so I couldn't
tell a stranger.

129
00:07:03,125 --> 00:07:04,250
A stranger?

130
00:07:04,333 --> 00:07:05,708
It happens all the time!

131
00:07:05,791 --> 00:07:08,208
Some random person leaks a
celebrity's private account

132
00:07:08,291 --> 00:07:09,500
and then they get spammed.

133
00:07:09,583 --> 00:07:10,875
[YUU gasps]
Oh, right.

134
00:07:10,958 --> 00:07:12,958
You wouldn't know since
you don't have a cell phone

135
00:07:13,041 --> 00:07:14,833
Do you understand
what "spammed" means?

136
00:07:14,916 --> 00:07:17,125
It's like when you get
bombarded online.

137
00:07:17,208 --> 00:07:18,375
I mean, since you
don't use Twitter,

138
00:07:18,458 --> 00:07:20,791
I bet this all sounds
pretty dumb to you!

139
00:07:20,875 --> 00:07:22,041
It's just dangerous--

140
00:07:22,125 --> 00:07:24,166
So, you thought if you
told a stranger like me,

141
00:07:24,250 --> 00:07:26,833
I'd freak out and blab
to everybody, right?

142
00:07:26,916 --> 00:07:29,125
Wha--? Uh, no. It's not that.

143
00:07:29,208 --> 00:07:31,541
It's just that
on Twitter, it's--

144
00:07:31,625 --> 00:07:34,708
[FUUKA] I get it, okay?
Don't make fun of me!

145
00:07:37,083 --> 00:07:39,875
I don't get why it's
turning out like this.

146
00:07:45,791 --> 00:07:49,750
[sighs] Why'd it have
to turn out like this?

147
00:08:01,416 --> 00:08:03,416
[YUU, FUUKA gasp]

148
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:05,166
[YUU gasps]

149
00:08:06,791 --> 00:08:08,500
[MIKASA gasps]

150
00:08:08,583 --> 00:08:10,708
[YAHAGI]
Huh?

151
00:08:10,791 --> 00:08:13,500
[TOMOMI] Hey, everyone!
Not working too hard, are you?

152
00:08:13,583 --> 00:08:15,333
Uh. Miss, Tomomi, hello!

153
00:08:15,416 --> 00:08:18,208
You brought Nachi
senpai with you?

154
00:08:18,291 --> 00:08:20,958
I came to see how
you were doing!

155
00:08:22,208 --> 00:08:23,333
[NACHI grunts]

156
00:08:23,416 --> 00:08:25,041
[BOTH]
Uh...

157
00:08:34,250 --> 00:08:35,833
[NACHI] Come back to
Tokyo with me right now

158
00:08:35,916 --> 00:08:38,541
and join the track team!
It isn't too late.

159
00:08:38,625 --> 00:08:40,541
Please don't start
with that again.

160
00:08:40,625 --> 00:08:43,750
I don't get it, what are you
even doing here, Nachi?

161
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:45,833
Miss Tomomi told me at
school that the three of you

162
00:08:45,916 --> 00:08:47,500
were working here
for the summer.

163
00:08:47,583 --> 00:08:50,375
So I made her bring me along so
we could talk about track!

164
00:08:50,458 --> 00:08:51,958
You had nothing better to do?

165
00:08:52,041 --> 00:08:53,208
[NACHI]
What?!

166
00:08:53,291 --> 00:08:54,750
I'm beginning to think
maybe I should've kept

167
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:56,333
their summer job to myself.

168
00:08:56,416 --> 00:08:59,458
The way things are going, I'm
pretty sure I'd have to agree.

169
00:08:59,541 --> 00:09:00,833
Hey, Haruna.

170
00:09:00,916 --> 00:09:02,750
You think Fuuka should join
the track team, right?

171
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:05,416
Uh... I, well, I don't know.

172
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:07,708
[MIKASA] You shouldn't keep
pressuring her, Senpai.

173
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:12,125
Forcing someone to do
something they don't want,

174
00:09:12,208 --> 00:09:14,458
that never yields
good results.

175
00:09:14,541 --> 00:09:16,416
Yuu agrees with me,
right man?

176
00:09:16,500 --> 00:09:19,083
Uh, sure.

177
00:09:19,166 --> 00:09:20,166
[NACHI grunts]

178
00:09:20,250 --> 00:09:22,166
[YUU]
Uh...

179
00:09:22,250 --> 00:09:24,458
[FUUKA]
Jeez! Would you give it a rest?

180
00:09:24,541 --> 00:09:27,125
I've already decided.
I'm gonna make music!

181
00:09:27,208 --> 00:09:28,375
And we'll work our butts off

182
00:09:28,458 --> 00:09:30,500
and become an awesome
band like the Hedgehogs!

183
00:09:30,583 --> 00:09:33,250
Oh, wow!, Hearing you call
the Hedgehogs awesome

184
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:35,333
is making me blush!

185
00:09:35,416 --> 00:09:36,625
[ALL]
Huh?

186
00:09:38,083 --> 00:09:40,666
Why would calling them
awesome make you blush?

187
00:09:40,750 --> 00:09:43,375
Come on, stop teasing.
Haven't you noticed?

188
00:09:43,458 --> 00:09:45,541
Uh, no.

189
00:09:45,625 --> 00:09:49,875
Uh. Hey, wait!, I think
I know who you are!

190
00:09:49,958 --> 00:09:52,708
You're the guitarist for
the Hedgehogs! Hisa!

191
00:09:52,791 --> 00:09:55,208
Uh-huh. There it is.

192
00:09:55,291 --> 00:09:59,083
[TOMOMI] You got it!
So you know who I am now?

193
00:09:59,166 --> 00:10:02,541
[YUU]
Hm... Maybe their manager?

194
00:10:02,625 --> 00:10:06,541
[gasps]
I'm the keyboardist, Tomo!

195
00:10:08,458 --> 00:10:10,333
[FUUKA]
Huh...? Huh?

196
00:10:10,416 --> 00:10:11,750
[TOMOMI whimpers]

197
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:14,125
And of course you know,
Yassan's our drummer, right?

198
00:10:14,208 --> 00:10:16,000
[FUUKA]
What?!

199
00:10:17,375 --> 00:10:18,791
[YAHAGI]
Huh?

200
00:10:21,708 --> 00:10:24,333
[FUUKA] Why didn't you tell
us this before now, huh?

201
00:10:24,416 --> 00:10:26,875
[TOMOMI] I thought it'd
be fun to surprise you.

202
00:10:26,958 --> 00:10:29,750
It's not like there was a
reason to come out and say it.

203
00:10:29,833 --> 00:10:32,416
I can't believe I didn't
recognize you guys.

204
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:35,500
We've all gotten older, so we
look pretty different now.

205
00:10:35,583 --> 00:10:38,416
I mean, look at Yassan.
He's already an old man.

206
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:39,958
Hey, Shut up.

207
00:10:40,041 --> 00:10:41,166
I could've asked questions

208
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:43,125
and learned so much
from you if I'd known!

209
00:10:43,208 --> 00:10:45,458
I am an enormous fan
of the Hedgehogs!

210
00:10:45,541 --> 00:10:48,708
Same here, I'm a huge fan, too!
I listen to your CD every day!

211
00:10:48,791 --> 00:10:50,208
So? I do, too!

212
00:10:50,291 --> 00:10:51,291
[BOTH grunt]

213
00:10:51,375 --> 00:10:53,500
Uhh, Thanks,

214
00:10:53,583 --> 00:10:55,291
[FUUKA, YUU sigh]

215
00:11:03,750 --> 00:11:08,875
So, wait a minute, Where are the
other members, Tama and Nico?

216
00:11:08,958 --> 00:11:11,125
Those two disappeared
a little while back.

217
00:11:11,208 --> 00:11:12,666
[FUUKA]
Huh?

218
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:14,833
Yeah, Tama just left out of
the blue without a word to us,

219
00:11:14,916 --> 00:11:16,500
and then Nico took
off after her,

220
00:11:16,583 --> 00:11:18,333
determined to track her down.

221
00:11:18,416 --> 00:11:20,541
Well, that seems weird.

222
00:11:20,625 --> 00:11:22,875
That's actually why the
band has been on a hiatus.

223
00:11:22,958 --> 00:11:24,375
'Cause we've been
waiting around for 'em.

224
00:11:24,458 --> 00:11:26,958
Yeah, they've been
gone for a while,

225
00:11:27,041 --> 00:11:30,583
but we know they'll
come back eventually.

226
00:11:30,666 --> 00:11:34,333
Hey, Yassan. When we get back
to Tokyo, you gotta teach us!

227
00:11:34,416 --> 00:11:37,041
I promise, we'll do our
best to be like you guys!

228
00:11:37,125 --> 00:11:40,041
Woah, You're a pretty
impulsive kid, aren't you?

229
00:11:40,125 --> 00:11:41,750
[NACHI]
Hang on a minute, Fuuka.

230
00:11:41,833 --> 00:11:43,583
What's your problem now?

231
00:11:43,666 --> 00:11:45,875
This is pretty ridiculous.

232
00:11:45,958 --> 00:11:48,375
Do you really think it's that
easy for a random person

233
00:11:48,458 --> 00:11:49,833
to become a pro?

234
00:11:49,916 --> 00:11:53,708
Well, no. Of course I don't
think it'll be easy, but--

235
00:11:53,791 --> 00:11:55,125
Listen to me!

236
00:11:55,208 --> 00:11:57,583
You know the track team's
a much better fit for you!

237
00:11:57,666 --> 00:12:01,500
You can't even say for sure
that you have musical talent!

238
00:12:03,083 --> 00:12:04,166
I say she does!

239
00:12:04,250 --> 00:12:05,625
[gasps]

240
00:12:05,708 --> 00:12:10,541
I've heard her sing before.
She's really wonderful.

241
00:12:10,625 --> 00:12:13,250
You've heard her?

242
00:12:13,333 --> 00:12:15,833
[gasps]

243
00:12:15,916 --> 00:12:17,041
[YAHAGI]
Uh...

244
00:12:17,125 --> 00:12:19,791
[TOMOMI sighs]

245
00:12:19,875 --> 00:12:22,750
Okay. Why don't
we test her, then?

246
00:12:26,625 --> 00:12:29,791
Man, this is such
a pain in my ass.

247
00:12:29,875 --> 00:12:31,333
Such a complainer.

248
00:12:31,416 --> 00:12:33,708
So, she's really gonna
try out in front of the pros

249
00:12:33,791 --> 00:12:35,791
using one of
their own songs?

250
00:12:35,875 --> 00:12:37,875
There's no way she
can handle that.

251
00:12:37,958 --> 00:12:40,041
Once they give her
their brutal review,

252
00:12:40,125 --> 00:12:43,041
you'll stop encouraging
her to do this, right?

253
00:12:44,625 --> 00:12:45,625
[YUU]
But...

254
00:12:49,916 --> 00:12:51,833
...I know she can do it,

255
00:12:51,916 --> 00:12:54,041
[YAHAGI]
Haruna! C'mere a sec.

256
00:12:54,125 --> 00:12:55,500
Yeah, I'm coming.

257
00:12:58,750 --> 00:13:00,333
This bass belonged to Nico.

258
00:13:00,416 --> 00:13:02,375
I think you should
play it, today.

259
00:13:02,458 --> 00:13:03,791
Wha--?

260
00:13:03,875 --> 00:13:06,083
I've never even touched a bass,
let alone played one.

261
00:13:06,166 --> 00:13:09,708
No worries, no one expects a
newbie to play it exactly right.

262
00:13:09,791 --> 00:13:12,000
All you have to do is hold
down these two strings

263
00:13:12,083 --> 00:13:13,666
in time with the song.

264
00:13:13,750 --> 00:13:15,458
And this one on the chorus.

265
00:13:17,708 --> 00:13:20,375
Here, Try to use this thing.

266
00:13:20,458 --> 00:13:21,958
[YUU]
Uh...

267
00:13:22,041 --> 00:13:24,375
Not quite, that's upside down.

268
00:13:26,791 --> 00:13:30,208
[MIKASA]
Yuu. Do you have a second?

269
00:13:35,208 --> 00:13:37,708
[YUU]
So, what's up?

270
00:13:37,791 --> 00:13:40,375
Be honest, are you and
Fuuka still having a fight?

271
00:13:40,458 --> 00:13:42,750
Oh, I dunno,

272
00:13:42,833 --> 00:13:45,583
Well, did you ever try
really talking to her?

273
00:13:45,666 --> 00:13:48,916
I really want to, but it
never comes out right.

274
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:50,625
I think you're both
letting your pride

275
00:13:50,708 --> 00:13:52,875
get in the way of
your own happiness.

276
00:13:52,958 --> 00:13:54,833
[YUU gasps]

277
00:13:54,916 --> 00:13:58,333
You want to make up,
isn't that right?

278
00:13:58,416 --> 00:14:00,333
Yeah.

279
00:14:00,416 --> 00:14:02,541
When I'm fighting with Akitsuki,

280
00:14:02,625 --> 00:14:06,041
I can't enjoy my work or
any other part of my day,

281
00:14:06,125 --> 00:14:08,791
And the hours seem
so much longer.

282
00:14:08,875 --> 00:14:11,291
When I eat, it feels
like I'm choking,

283
00:14:11,375 --> 00:14:13,708
and nothing tastes good.

284
00:14:13,791 --> 00:14:17,833
Even sitting out by the ocean
feels lonely without her.

285
00:14:17,916 --> 00:14:20,041
I think maybe I'm just
no good for anything

286
00:14:20,125 --> 00:14:22,791
if she's not smiling
next to me.

287
00:14:22,875 --> 00:14:27,416
So, yeah... I want to make up.

288
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:29,000
Good for you, but I
think the lesson here

289
00:14:29,083 --> 00:14:31,541
is you should've just
told her all of that.

290
00:14:31,625 --> 00:14:33,208
Isn't that right, Fuuka?

291
00:14:33,291 --> 00:14:34,458
[YUU gasps]

292
00:14:36,541 --> 00:14:39,291
[FUUKA whimpers]

293
00:14:39,375 --> 00:14:42,125
[YUU gasps]
Why'd you do that?

294
00:14:42,208 --> 00:14:44,666
[MIKASA] 'Cause she was
feeling the same as you.

295
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:47,583
Said she had no idea
how to apologize, either.

296
00:14:49,041 --> 00:14:51,166
[whimpers]

297
00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:53,541
You two can handle it
on your own from here.

298
00:14:53,625 --> 00:14:56,041
[YUU]
What? Mikasa, wait!

299
00:15:04,041 --> 00:15:05,833
[YUU] I think I blurted
out way more than I

300
00:15:05,916 --> 00:15:07,916
ever wanted her to hear,

301
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:11,375
"Maybe I'm just no good if
she's not smiling next to me."

302
00:15:11,458 --> 00:15:14,125
What was that? A confession?

303
00:15:16,125 --> 00:15:17,500
[gulps]

304
00:15:20,833 --> 00:15:23,333
Stupid.

305
00:15:23,416 --> 00:15:25,166
I'm sorry.

306
00:15:25,250 --> 00:15:28,916
[YUU]
Oh, no. I'm sorry, really.

307
00:15:33,666 --> 00:15:38,833
[FUUKA] And, listen. Thank you
for sticking up for me earlier.

308
00:15:43,333 --> 00:15:44,708
[grunts]

309
00:16:02,625 --> 00:16:05,791
Not bad, that bass suits you.
You look cool!

310
00:16:05,875 --> 00:16:08,375
Wha--? You really think so?

311
00:16:09,875 --> 00:16:12,750
I'm ready, I'll sing my best.

312
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:21,416
Welp, she's got some
stage presence at least.

313
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:24,250
[YAHAGI chuckles]
Let's do this.

314
00:16:28,833 --> 00:16:29,500
♪

315
00:16:29,583 --> 00:16:30,750
[gasps]

316
00:16:45,041 --> 00:16:47,500
♪ The place that I always
dreamed I'd reach one day ♪

317
00:16:47,583 --> 00:16:50,250
♪ is too high above
us to get to ♪

318
00:16:50,333 --> 00:16:52,125
♪ The promise we made is ♪

319
00:16:52,208 --> 00:16:55,625
♪ fading every moment
we conform like they do ♪

320
00:16:55,708 --> 00:16:57,166
♪ I wanna move on my own ♪

321
00:16:57,250 --> 00:17:00,000
♪ Step away from the crowd
I wanna dance to my own beat ♪

322
00:17:00,083 --> 00:17:03,291
♪ I'm done trying
to blend in ♪

323
00:17:03,375 --> 00:17:06,125
♪ I won't be tied to
a tedious world ♪

324
00:17:06,208 --> 00:17:09,208
♪ Repeating each day like a
broken record sickens me ♪

325
00:17:09,291 --> 00:17:11,666
♪ No matter how I try
I can't escape repetition ♪

326
00:17:11,750 --> 00:17:14,250
♪ It's hard to change it up
When no one else is listening ♪

327
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:16,041
♪ We're in a box,
stuck in a box ♪

328
00:17:16,125 --> 00:17:18,416
♪ Meant to stifle
what we feel ♪

329
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:21,250
♪ Forced to erase all
that we know is real ♪

330
00:17:21,333 --> 00:17:22,791
♪ But I refuse to
be locked up ♪

331
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:26,750
♪ Won't live in this prison
Gotta fight for open skies ♪

332
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:27,750
♪ Time to break free ♪

333
00:17:27,833 --> 00:17:29,291
♪ Open our hearts
to a world ♪

334
00:17:29,375 --> 00:17:32,541
♪ and go racing forward
to the light ♪

335
00:17:32,625 --> 00:17:33,916
♪ These broken chains
can't hold us back... ♪

336
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:35,416
♪ Wow, What's that? ♪

337
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:40,416
I remember this song,
I'm just trying to place it.

338
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:41,791
"Climber's High"
by the Hedgehogs.

339
00:17:41,875 --> 00:17:42,916
One of my favorites.

340
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:44,958
Yeah, that's what it is!

341
00:17:45,041 --> 00:17:49,250
They must be a cover band,
But they sound pretty good!

342
00:17:49,333 --> 00:17:51,541
It brings back memories.

343
00:17:51,625 --> 00:17:54,541
♪

344
00:17:54,625 --> 00:17:56,666
Koyuki, we're loaded up
and ready to go.

345
00:17:56,750 --> 00:17:58,666
'Kay, thanks.

346
00:17:58,750 --> 00:18:02,000
♪

347
00:18:02,083 --> 00:18:03,625
Is this for TV or something?

348
00:18:03,708 --> 00:18:06,583
Dunno, but I'm digging this
girl's voice. She's great!

349
00:18:06,666 --> 00:18:07,583
What's going on?

350
00:18:07,666 --> 00:18:08,583
Looks like a band.

351
00:18:08,666 --> 00:18:10,125
Let's go check it out!

352
00:18:10,208 --> 00:18:11,750
♪ Feel a pulsing
that reaches ♪

353
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:13,125
♪ Out to the limits ♪

354
00:18:13,208 --> 00:18:15,916
♪ Blowing fear away
with a vengeance ♪

355
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:18,333
♪ Growing faster
with every moment ♪

356
00:18:18,416 --> 00:18:21,250
♪ Closing up the distance that
once seemed to be unending ♪

357
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:22,791
♪ Out of my despair ♪

358
00:18:22,875 --> 00:18:23,958
♪ I can finally see ♪

359
00:18:24,041 --> 00:18:25,458
♪ A new and perfect world ♪

360
00:18:25,541 --> 00:18:26,750
♪ That's spread out
before me ♪

361
00:18:26,833 --> 00:18:28,916
♪ No more walls
to close me in ♪

362
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:32,166
♪ An endless sky
of blue above ♪

363
00:18:39,416 --> 00:18:42,375
[CROWD cheers]

364
00:18:42,458 --> 00:18:43,833
That was awesome!

365
00:18:43,916 --> 00:18:46,125
What is this for? Is there,
like, a festival going on?

366
00:18:48,166 --> 00:18:50,916
Man, How did she do that?

367
00:18:52,416 --> 00:18:54,416
[giggles]

368
00:18:57,416 --> 00:18:59,750
Oh my gosh, that felt
so amazing!

369
00:18:59,833 --> 00:19:02,083
How was the singing? Okay?

370
00:19:02,166 --> 00:19:03,916
If you ask me?
It was rough,

371
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:06,916
but you've got potential.
You should keep it up.

372
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:10,375
[FUUKA cheers]
You hear that, Nachi?

373
00:19:10,458 --> 00:19:12,166
I got approved by a pro!

374
00:19:12,250 --> 00:19:16,500
Yeah, do whatever you want,
I still think it's a mistake.

375
00:19:16,583 --> 00:19:19,375
Sure, you say that now, but you
know you were tapping along

376
00:19:19,458 --> 00:19:20,333
through the whole thing.

377
00:19:20,416 --> 00:19:21,250
Were you, really?

378
00:19:21,333 --> 00:19:22,833
[NACHI gasps]
Liar!

379
00:19:22,916 --> 00:19:25,000
If I was, it was only out of
habit from when my brother

380
00:19:25,083 --> 00:19:26,958
used to make me play
drums for his band!

381
00:19:27,041 --> 00:19:29,666
Wait, I have the best idea.

382
00:19:29,750 --> 00:19:33,500
You, Senpai, are gonna
be our drummer!

383
00:19:33,583 --> 00:19:35,083
Huh?

384
00:19:35,166 --> 00:19:37,375
[FUUKA] Makoto will be
on keys, and of course,

385
00:19:37,458 --> 00:19:38,291
Yuu will be our bassist.

386
00:19:38,375 --> 00:19:39,708
[YUU]
Huh?

387
00:19:39,791 --> 00:19:41,875
[FUUKA] And I'll be on guitar!
Our band is complete!

388
00:19:41,958 --> 00:19:44,916
[NACHI]
Hang on! Do I get a say in this?

389
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:49,083
As soon as we get back to Tokyo,
we have to start practicing!

390
00:19:49,166 --> 00:19:52,166
It was almost like we had
Tama back with us again.

391
00:19:52,250 --> 00:19:53,750
You prob'ly could've
been a little nicer to her,

392
00:19:53,833 --> 00:19:55,208
dontcha think?

393
00:19:55,291 --> 00:19:58,208
You're an idiot. That would've
given her a big head.

394
00:19:58,291 --> 00:20:00,791
Besides, you really think
this bunch of total amateurs

395
00:20:00,875 --> 00:20:02,333
can make a go of it?

396
00:20:02,416 --> 00:20:06,541
I think you forget. Sometimes
one person is all it takes.

397
00:20:08,166 --> 00:20:13,875
[TOMOMI] One special person,
of overwhelming talent.

398
00:20:31,333 --> 00:20:32,625
[YUU]
Mm?

399
00:20:45,625 --> 00:20:46,750
Hey, Yuu, what's up?

400
00:20:46,833 --> 00:20:48,375
What are you doing out here?

401
00:20:48,458 --> 00:20:50,458
Well, since we're
going home soon,

402
00:20:50,541 --> 00:20:53,833
I wanted to take a better look
at the stars before we left.

403
00:21:10,791 --> 00:21:12,333
So beautiful.

404
00:21:14,541 --> 00:21:15,791
[FUUKA gasps]

405
00:21:15,875 --> 00:21:18,875
Are you okay? Dressed like that,
you must be cold.

406
00:21:18,958 --> 00:21:21,166
[FUUKA] Yeah, hey, would you
let me use half of that?

407
00:21:21,250 --> 00:21:24,000
[YUU]
Uh, wha--?

408
00:21:24,083 --> 00:21:28,916
[FUUKA sighs, giggles]
See? Now I'm warm!

409
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:30,250
[gasps]

410
00:21:36,166 --> 00:21:38,458
[FUUKA]
You gonna post it on Twitter?

411
00:21:38,541 --> 00:21:42,125
[YUU] No, I don't think so.
It wouldn't do it justice.

412
00:21:43,916 --> 00:21:45,083
See? a black screen.

413
00:21:45,166 --> 00:21:48,750
Oh, wow, it is! Can't do
much with that, can ya?

414
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:50,416
[FUUKA giggles]

415
00:21:57,541 --> 00:21:59,875
[YUU] Guess we should
probably head back.

416
00:21:59,958 --> 00:22:00,875
[FUUKA]
Huh?

417
00:22:08,583 --> 00:22:11,000
Um...

418
00:22:11,083 --> 00:22:14,750
Well, I'm embarrassed,
I swear this wasn't on purpose!

419
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:17,958
[FUUKA growls]
You perv!

420
00:22:18,041 --> 00:22:19,833
--[smack]
--[YUU groans]

421
00:22:20,291 --> 00:22:31,875
♪

422
00:22:31,958 --> 00:22:34,583
<i>Looking up at the sky</i>
<i>I felt an emptiness</i>

423
00:22:34,666 --> 00:22:37,500
<i>All the colors of</i>
<i>summer have been faded</i>

424
00:22:37,583 --> 00:22:41,125
<i>Before I even knew the things</i>
<i>that made me the happiest</i>

425
00:22:41,208 --> 00:22:43,125
<i>Were hidden and tucked away</i>

426
00:22:43,208 --> 00:22:45,958
<i>But when I looked at you</i>
<i>it all felt so intense</i>

427
00:22:46,041 --> 00:22:48,833
<i>Your eyes cut to the</i>
<i>core of my existence</i>

428
00:22:48,916 --> 00:22:52,291
<i>Every word that you spoke</i>
<i>was like a painting in every hue</i>

429
00:22:52,375 --> 00:22:54,125
<i>You brought calm into my world</i>

430
00:22:54,208 --> 00:22:56,666
<i>All I can do now is breathe</i>

431
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:59,625
<i>And figure out just what I need</i>

432
00:22:59,708 --> 00:23:02,208
<i>Resolve myself, pursue my dreams</i>

433
00:23:02,291 --> 00:23:04,750
<i>I'm running</i>

434
00:23:04,833 --> 00:23:07,541
<i>Moving forward, taking your hand</i>

435
00:23:07,625 --> 00:23:08,916
<i>Being with you</i>

436
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:10,583
<i>I'm finally free enough to</i>
<i>spread out my wings</i>

437
00:23:10,666 --> 00:23:13,083
<i>Let's catch the wind</i>
<i>and go for a ride</i>

438
00:23:13,166 --> 00:23:17,000
<i>You and I can fly</i>
<i>anywhere together</i>

439
00:23:17,083 --> 00:23:19,416
<i>We can go as high</i>
<i>up as we want</i>

440
00:23:19,500 --> 00:23:22,208
<i>Following the path that's</i>
<i>been laid pout before us</i>

441
00:23:22,291 --> 00:23:25,833
<i>Guided by our</i>
<i>bonded hearts forever</i>

442
00:23:25,916 --> 00:23:29,250
<i>Let's keep living</i>
<i>out this fantasy</i>

443
00:23:29,333 --> 00:23:33,250
<i>And chasing our dreams</i>

444
00:23:33,333 --> 00:23:36,583
<i>Ah... Ah...</i>

445
00:23:36,666 --> 00:23:41,625
♪

446
00:23:53,291 --> 00:23:56,083
Feels like it's been forever
since I've been home.

447
00:23:58,958 --> 00:24:00,250
At least they can't complain.

448
00:24:00,333 --> 00:24:03,166
I remembered to get them
all some souvenirs.

449
00:24:03,250 --> 00:24:04,916
I'm home, Hey,!

450
00:24:06,250 --> 00:24:09,875
Oh! Welcome back home, Nico!

451
00:24:09,958 --> 00:24:11,541
Thanks, Tama,

452
00:24:13,833 --> 00:24:15,916
[FUUKA]
Next time, "One of Us!"

